<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 14 at 7:14AM EDT  by NWS Cleveland</headline>
<description>...Line of showers with gusty winds will impact portions of Portage,
Trumbull, Mahoning, southeastern Geauga, Stark, Ashtabula, Erie and
Crawford Counties through 800 AM EDT...
At 713 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of showers along a
line extending from 30 miles northwest of Girard to near Burton to
near Sugarcreek. Movement was east at 50 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Erie, Canton, Youngstown, Warren, Ashtabula, Meadville, Conneaut,
Ravenna, Boardman, Alliance, Niles, North Canton, Louisville,
Campbell, Hubbard, Canfield, Cortland, Corry, Edinboro and Geneva.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
